members.member:
Applies an oil-painting effect to the image.
You control the effect by specifying the size of the neighborhood that is used for calculating the pixel value. For example, for 8x8, set 8 in the Dimension property or pass 8 inthe dimension parameter of the Constructor. You increase the size of the neighborhood in order to decrease the amount of detail in the resulting image.
This command supports 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images. Support for 12 and 16-bit grayscale and 48 and 64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.
This command does not support signed data images.
This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.
For more information, refer to Applying Artistic Effects.
